CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 4, 1960, pg. 1, reads: "Three Die in Auto Crash - In this car, which slammed against a Moon Township Abutment shortly before midnight on Saturday. Andrew Burton, the driver; Saul Davis (inset) and William Wells were killed.  Claude King, also of Coraopolis, a passenger in rear seat on the right side (side facing you), miraculously escaped death and is recovering in Sewickley Hospital - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Wrecked Buick car driven by Andrew Burton after fatal crash, with tow truck on right, Moon Township
